# calc_semantic_parentheses.numos — grouping overrides precedence: (2 + 3) * 4 == 20.
#
# Phase 8C semantic smoke. NO screenshot, NO golden.
#
# NumOS note: the close-paren key is a no-op (RPAREN has no handler); a paren is a
# VPAM container you exit with RIGHT, exactly like a fraction. So the sequence is
# `(` 2 + 3 RIGHT * 4 — RIGHT leaves the parenthesised group before the `* 4`.
# (Empirically: using a literal `)` instead of RIGHT keeps the cursor inside the
# group and yields 2+3*4=14, so RIGHT is required to get 20.)
#
# Run: program --headless --deterministic --script <this> --frames 1400 --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 parse · 3 screenshot · 4 assertion failure.

log "calc_semantic_parentheses: waiting for launcher"
wait 200
open_app Calculation
wait 60

key (
key 2
key +
key 3
key RIGHT
key *
key 4
key ENTER
wait 120

assert_app Calculation
assert_no_error
assert_result 20
log "calc_semantic_parentheses: PASS ((2 + 3) * 4 == 20)"
